    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our premier start; his 82.13 score is driven by a massive +19% SP skill advantage against Sasaki and a +14% platoon edge, further bolstered by wind conditions favoring an outfielder with his profile. **Junior Caminero** (73.53) and **Trea Turner** (68.86) provide the high-floor stability we demand, with **Trea Turner** benefiting significantly from his projected leadoff spot and a soft matchup against Elder. While **Kyle Schwarber** (65.76) faces the same starter, his elite 0.402 xwOBA makes him a cornerstone play in the heart of our order. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Colt Keith** (62.83) and **Yordan Alvarez** (62.54), both of whom offer strong upside despite the latter facing a slightly more difficult internal platoon hurdle against a left-handed starter.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card was the exclusion of **Victor Scott II**. With a score of 39.50, he landed just shy of our 40.00 efficiency floor, largely due to a difficult draw against Woo and the inherent volatility of a #9 spot in the batting order. While his elite sprint speed remains a top-tier asset for our stolen base-starved roster, the math dictates we preserve our limited game caps when the matchup profile dips this low. Meanwhile, we continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar**, both of whom remain sidelined on the IL, as well as **Zac Veen**, who is currently working to earn a call-up from Albuquerque.\n\nOur remaining depth pieces\u2014**Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, and **Hyeseong Kim**\u2014all currently sit in the \"marginal\" 40\u201359 range. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Hyeseong Kim**, as the opposing pitcher\u2019s 63% success rate at holding runners negates some of the upside we usually expect from his speed profile. All managers should note that the lineups for **Gary Sanchez**, **Trea Turner**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Kyle Schwarber** are currently pending; should these assignments shift significantly downward, we will need to re-evaluate our game cap exposure before the first pitch. We remain deep in alternatives like **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, and **Luis Pena** should the late-afternoon updates force a pivot.",
